<span id="iv.iii.xl-p1"></span> <span class="c6"><span
id="iv.iii.xl-p1.1"></span>Section XL.</span>

<span id="iv.iii.xl-p2"></span>\[1\] \[Arabic, p. 150\]  <span
id="fr_2716"></span>[2717](#fn_2716.md) And when Jesus entered the temple,
they brought unto him blind and \[2\] lame:  and he healed them.   <span
id="fr_2717"></span>[2718](#fn_2717.md) But when the chief priests and the
Pharisees saw the wonders that he did, and the children that were crying
in the temple and \[3\] saying, Praise be to the Son of David:  it
distressed them,  <span id="fr_2718"></span>[2719](#fn_2718.md) and they
said, Hearest thou not what these say?  Jesus said unto them, Yea:  did
ye not read long ago, From \[4\] the mouths of children and infants thou
hast chosen my praise?   <span id="fr_2719"></span>[2720](#fn_2719.md) And
the Pharisees said one to another, Behold, do ye not see that nothing
availeth us? for lo, the whole world hath followed him.

<span id="iv.iii.xl-p7"></span>\[5\]  <span
id="fr_2720"></span>[2721](#fn_2720.md) And there were among them certain
Gentiles also, which had come up to worship \[6\] at the feast:   <span
id="fr_2721"></span>[2722](#fn_2721.md) these therefore came to Philip, who
was of Bethsaida of Galilee, \[7\] and asked him, and said unto him, My
lord, we wish to see Jesus.   <span id="fr_2722"></span>[2723](#fn_2722.md)
And Philip \[8\] came and told Andrew:  and Andrew and Philip told
Jesus.   <span id="fr_2723"></span>[2724](#fn_2723.md) And Jesus answered
and said unto them, The hour is come nigh, in which the Son of man is to
be glorified.  \[9\]  <span id="fr_2724"></span>[2725](#fn_2724.md) Verily,
verily, I say unto you, A grain of wheat, if it fall not and die in the
\[10\] earth, remaineth alone; but if it die, it beareth much fruit. 
 <span id="fr_2725"></span>[2726](#fn_2725.md) He that loveth his
life <span id="fr_2726"></span>[2727](#fn_2726.md) destroyeth it; and he
that hateth his life <span id="fr_2727"></span>[2728](#fn_2727.md) in this
world shall keep it unto the life eternal.  \[11\]  <span
id="fr_2728"></span>[2729](#fn_2728.md) If a man serve me, he will follow
me; and where I am, there shall my servant be \[12\] also:  and
whosoever serveth me, the Father will honour him.   <span
id="fr_2729"></span>[2730](#fn_2729.md) Now is my soul troubled:  \[Arabic,
p. 151\] and what shall I say?  My Father, deliver me from this hour. 
But \[13\] for this cause came I unto this hour.   <span
id="fr_2730"></span>[2731](#fn_2730.md) My Father, glorify thy name.  And a
\[14\] voice was heard from heaven, I have glorified *it*, and shall
glorify *it*.   <span id="fr_2731"></span>[2732](#fn_2731.md) And the
multitude that were standing heard, and said, This is thunder:  and
others said, An \[15\] angel speaketh to him.   <span
id="fr_2732"></span>[2733](#fn_2732.md) Jesus answered and said unto them,
Not because of me \[16\] was this voice, but because of you.   <span
id="fr_2733"></span>[2734](#fn_2733.md) Now is the judgement of this world;
and the \[17\] prince of this world shall now be cast forth.   <span
id="fr_2734"></span>[2735](#fn_2734.md) And I, when I am lifted up from the
\[18\] earth, shall draw every man unto me.   <span
id="fr_2735"></span>[2736](#fn_2735.md) This he said, that he might shew by
what \[19\] manner of death he should die.   <span
id="fr_2736"></span>[2737](#fn_2736.md) The multitudes said unto him, We
have heard out of the law that the Messiah abideth for ever:  how then
sayest thou, that the Son of \[20\] man is to be lifted up? who is this,
the Son of man?   <span id="fr_2737"></span>[2738](#fn_2737.md) Jesus said
unto them, Another little while is the light with you.  Walk so long as
ye have light, lest the darkness overtake you; for he that walketh in
the darkness knoweth not whither he goeth.  \[21\]  <span
id="fr_2738"></span>[2739](#fn_2738.md) So long as ye have light, believe
the light, that ye may be the children of the light.

<span id="iv.iii.xl-p27"></span>\[22\]  <span
id="fr_2739"></span>[2740](#fn_2739.md) And when certain of the Pharisees
asked of Jesus, when the kingdom of God should come, he answered and
said unto them, The kingdom of God cometh not <span id="page_105">p.
105</span> <span id="iv.iii.xl-Page_105"></span>\[23\] with
expectation:   <span id="fr_2740"></span>[2741](#fn_2740.md) neither shall
they say, Lo, it is here! nor, Lo, it is there! for the kingdom of God
is within you.

<span id="iv.iii.xl-p30"></span>\[24\]  <span
id="fr_2741"></span>[2742](#fn_2741.md) And in the day*time* he was
teaching in the temple; and at night he used to go \[25\] out, and pass
the night in the mount called the mount of Olives.   <span
id="fr_2742"></span>[2743](#fn_2742.md) And all the people came <span
id="fr_2743"></span>[2744](#fn_2743.md) to him in the morning in the
temple, to hear his word.

<span id="iv.iii.xl-p34"></span>\[26, 27\]  <span
id="fr_2744"></span>[2745](#fn_2744.md) Then spake Jesus unto the
multitudes and his disciples, and said unto them,  <span
id="fr_2745"></span>[2746](#fn_2745.md) On \[28\] \[Arabic, p. 152\] the
seat of Moses are seated the scribes and Pharisees:   <span
id="fr_2746"></span>[2747](#fn_2746.md) everything that they say unto you
now to keep, keep and do:  but according to their deeds \[29\] do ye
not; for they say, and do not.   <span
id="fr_2747"></span>[2748](#fn_2747.md) And they bind heavy burdens, and
lay them on the shoulders of the people; while they with one of their
fingers will not come \[30, 31\] near <span
id="fr_2748"></span>[2749](#fn_2748.md) them.   <span
id="fr_2749"></span>[2750](#fn_2749.md) But all their deeds they do to make
a shew before men.   <span id="fr_2750"></span>[2751](#fn_2750.md) And all
the multitude were hearing that with pleasure.

<span id="iv.iii.xl-p42"></span>\[32\]  <span
id="fr_2751"></span>[2752](#fn_2751.md) And in the course of his teaching
he said unto them, Guard yourselves from the \[33\] scribes, who desire
to walk in robes,  <span id="fr_2752"></span>[2753](#fn_2752.md) and love
salutation in the marketplaces, and sitting in the highest places of the
synagogues, and at feasts in the highest parts of \[34\] the rooms: 
 <span id="fr_2753"></span>[2754](#fn_2753.md) and they broaden their
amulets, and lengthen the cords of their cloaks, \[35\]  <span
id="fr_2754"></span>[2755](#fn_2754.md) and *love* that they should be
called by men, My master,  <span id="fr_2755"></span>[2756](#fn_2755.md)
and devour widows’ houses, because <span
id="fr_2756"></span>[2757](#fn_2756.md) of their prolonging their prayers;
these then shall receive greater judgement.  \[36\]  <span
id="fr_2757"></span>[2758](#fn_2757.md) But ye, be ye not called
masters: <span id="fr_2758"></span>[2759](#fn_2758.md)   for your master is
one; all ye are brethren.  \[37\]  <span
id="fr_2759"></span>[2760](#fn_2759.md) Call not then to yourselves *any
one* <span id="fr_2760"></span>[2761](#fn_2760.md) father on earth:  for
your Father is one, who is \[38\] in heaven.   <span
id="fr_2761"></span>[2762](#fn_2761.md) And be not called directors:  for
your director is one, *even* the Messiah.  \[39, 40\]  <span
id="fr_2762"></span>[2763](#fn_2762.md) He that is great among you shall be
unto you a minister.   <span id="fr_2763"></span>[2764](#fn_2763.md)
Whosoever shall exalt himself shall be abased; and whosoever shall abase
himself shall be exalted.

<span id="iv.iii.xl-p56"></span>\[41\]  <span
id="fr_2764"></span>[2765](#fn_2764.md) Woe unto you, Pharisees! because ye
love the highest places in the synagogues, and salutation in the
marketplaces.

<span id="iv.iii.xl-p58"></span>\[42\]  <span
id="fr_2765"></span>[2766](#fn_2765.md) Woe unto you, scribes and
Pharisees, hypocrites! because ye devour widows’ houses, because <span
id="fr_2766"></span>[2767](#fn_2766.md) of your prolonging your prayers: 
for this *reason* then ye shall receive greater judgement.

<span id="iv.iii.xl-p61"></span>\[43\]  <span
id="fr_2767"></span>[2768](#fn_2767.md) Woe unto you, scribes and
Pharisees, hypocrites! because ye have shut the kingdom of God before
men.

<span id="iv.iii.xl-p63"></span>\[44\] \[Arabic, p. 153\]  <span
id="fr_2768"></span>[2769](#fn_2768.md) Woe unto you that know the law! for
ye concealed the keys of knowledge:   <span
id="fr_2769"></span>[2770](#fn_2769.md) ye enter not, and those that are
entering ye suffer not to enter.

<span id="iv.iii.xl-p66"></span>\[45\]  <span
id="fr_2770"></span>[2771](#fn_2770.md) Woe unto you, scribes and
Pharisees, hypocrites! because <span
id="fr_2771"></span>[2772](#fn_2771.md) ye compass land and sea to
draw <span id="fr_2772"></span>[2773](#fn_2772.md) one proselyte; and when
he is *become so*, ye make him a son of hell twice as much <span
id="fr_2773"></span>[2774](#fn_2773.md) as yourselves.

<span id="iv.iii.xl-p71"></span>\[46\]  <span
id="fr_2774"></span>[2775](#fn_2774.md) Woe unto you, ye blind guides!
because ye say, Whosoever sweareth by the temple, it is nothing; but
whosoever sweareth by the gold that is in the temple, \[47\] shall be
condemned. <span id="fr_2775"></span>[2776](#fn_2775.md)   <span
id="fr_2776"></span>[2777](#fn_2776.md) Ye blind foolish *ones*:  which is
greater, the gold, or the \[48\] temple which sanctifieth the gold? 
 <span id="fr_2777"></span>[2778](#fn_2777.md) And, Whosoever sweareth by
the altar, it is nothing; but whosoever sweareth by the offering that is
upon it, shall be condemned. <span id="fr_2778"></span>[2779](#fn_2778.md)
  \[49\]  <span id="fr_2779"></span>[2780](#fn_2779.md) Ye blind foolish
*ones*:  which is greater, the offering, or the altar which sanctifieth
\[50\] the offering?   <span id="fr_2780"></span>[2781](#fn_2780.md)
Whosoever then sweareth by the altar, hath sworn by it, and by all
\[51\] that is upon it.   <span id="fr_2781"></span>[2782](#fn_2781.md) And
whosoever sweareth by the temple, hath sworn by it, and by \[52\] him
that is dwelling in it.   <span id="fr_2782"></span>[2783](#fn_2782.md) And
whosoever sweareth by heaven, hath sworn by the throne of God, and by
him that sitteth upon it.

<span id="iv.iii.xl-p81"></span>\[53\]  <span
id="fr_2783"></span>[2784](#fn_2783.md) Woe unto you, scribes and
Pharisees, hypocrites! because ye tithe mint and rue and dill and cummin
and all herbs, and ye leave the important *matters* of the law,
judgement, and mercy, and faith, and the love of God:  this ought ye to
do, and \[54\] not to leave that *undone*.   <span
id="fr_2784"></span>[2785](#fn_2784.md) Ye blind guides, which strain out a
gnat, and swallow <span id="fr_2785"></span>[2786](#fn_2785.md) camels.

<span id="iv.iii.xl-p85"></span>\[55\]  <span
id="fr_2786"></span>[2787](#fn_2786.md) Woe unto you, scribes and
Pharisees, hypocrites! because ye cleanse the outside <span
id="page_106">p. 106</span> <span id="iv.iii.xl-Page_106"></span>of the
cup and of the platter, while the inside of them is full of injustice
and wrong.  \[56\]  <span id="fr_2787"></span>[2788](#fn_2787.md) Ye blind
Pharisees, cleanse first the inside of the cup and of the platter, then
shall the outside of them be cleansed.

<span id="iv.iii.xl-p88"></span>\[57\] \[Arabic, p. 154\]  <span
id="fr_2788"></span>[2789](#fn_2788.md) Woe unto you, scribes and
Pharisees, hypocrites! because ye resemble whited sepulchres, which
appear <span id="fr_2789"></span>[2790](#fn_2789.md) from the outside
beautiful, but within \[58\] full of the bones of the dead, and all
uncleanness.   <span id="fr_2790"></span>[2791](#fn_2790.md) So ye also
from without appear unto men like the righteous, but within ye are full
of wrong and hypocrisy.

<span id="iv.iii.xl-p92"></span>\[59\]  <span
id="fr_2791"></span>[2792](#fn_2791.md) One of the scribes answered and
said unto him, Teacher, in this saying of thine \[60\] thou art casting
a slur on us.   <span id="fr_2792"></span>[2793](#fn_2792.md) He said, And
to you also, ye scribes, woe! for ye lade men with heavy burdens, and ye
with one of your fingers come not near <span
id="fr_2793"></span>[2794](#fn_2793.md) those burdens.

<span id="iv.iii.xl-p96"></span>\[61\]  <span
id="fr_2794"></span>[2795](#fn_2794.md) Woe unto you, scribes and
Pharisees, hypocrites! for ye build the tombs of the prophets, which
your fathers killed, and adorn the burying-places of the righteous,
\[62\] and say,  <span id="fr_2795"></span>[2796](#fn_2795.md) If we had
been in the days of our fathers, we should not have been partakers
\[63\] with them in the blood of the prophets.   <span
id="fr_2796"></span>[2797](#fn_2796.md) Wherefore, behold, ye witness
against \[64\] yourselves, that ye are the children of those that slew
the prophets.   <span id="fr_2797"></span>[2798](#fn_2797.md) And ye also,
\[65\] ye fill up the measure <span id="fr_2798"></span>[2799](#fn_2798.md)
of your fathers.   <span id="fr_2799"></span>[2800](#fn_2799.md) Ye
serpents, ye children of vipers, where shall ye flee from the judgement
of Gehenna?

